Adding these estimated increases to the base melting point of benzene gives an overall prediction: 5.5 (benzene) + 100 (benzothiazole/benzonaphthyridine system) + 100 (second benzothiazole/benzonaphthyridine system) + 30 (nitrile group) + 40 (ketone group) + 10 (amine group) = 285.5°C.
